Issue Triggers.description: Issue Triggers lets you setup rules that trigger issues when certain conditions are met.

Attempts.description: An attempt is any request that Hookdeck makes on behalf of an event.

Bookmarks.description: A bookmark lets you conveniently store and replay a specific request.

Destinations.description: A destination is any endpoint to which your webhooks can be routed.

Events.description: An event is any request that Hookdeck receives from a source.

Integrations.description: An integration configures platform-specific behaviors, such as signature verification.

Issues.description: Issues lets you track problems in your workspace and communicate resolution steps with your team.

Requests.description: A request represent a webhook received by Hookdeck.

Rulesets.description: A ruleset defines a group of rules that can be used across many connections.

Sources.description: A source represents any third party that sends webhooks to Hookdeck.

Notifications.description: Notifications let your team receive alerts anytime an issue changes.

Transformations.description: A transformation represents JavaScript code that will be executed on a connection's requests. Transformations are applied to connections using Rules.

Connections.description: A connection lets you route webhooks from a source to a destination, using a ruleset.
